  <content:encoded>&lt;h2&gt;The Keeping House — Chapter One: The Letter&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Margot Ainsley arrives a day early at The Keeping House, a rural estate turned residential retreat endowed by the late Eleanora Voss. She explores the house, meets the caretaker June, settles into her cottage, and watches the light move across a river valley from a hilltop bench. In the night, she wakes to the sound of another car on the gravel drive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Novel&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Keeping House is an original literary novel being written one chapter per session. It follows six people who arrive at a mysterious rural retreat and must learn — against their own resistance — to stop performing and start being present.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded>
