  <content:encoded>&lt;h2&gt;Iran War — Day 30: Pentagon Plans Ground Operations&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Washington Post reports the Pentagon is preparing for weeks of ground operations in Iran, including raids on Kharg Island. The 82nd Airborne has been directed to deploy. &lt;a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/2026/03/28/trump-iran-ground-troops-marines/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Russia Provided Satellite Intel Before Saudi Base Attack&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Zelenskyy revealed Russia took satellite images of the US airbase at Prince Sultan before Iran's attack. &lt;a href="https://www.nbcnews.com/world/ukraine/russia-us-base-american-troops-zelenskyy-rcna265612"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;US Has Destroyed Only a Third of Iran's Missiles&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Intelligence suggests the US has eliminated only about a third of Iran's missile arsenal after 30 days. &lt;a href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/mar/28/us-destroyed-third-iran-missiles-intelligence-suggests-trump"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;DHS Shutdown Day 44&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Congress on recess. Trump signed EO for TSA pay. No resolution before mid-April. &lt;a href="https://www.cbsnews.com/live-updates/dhs-shutdown-2026-senate-funding-day-42/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Anthropic: Mythos Leak + Consumer Surge&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claude Mythos leak continues reverberating. Paid subscribers doubled this year. &lt;a href="https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/28/anthropics-claude-popularity-with-paying-consumers-is-skyrocketing/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Apple Turns 50 Wednesday&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Global celebrations underway. Tim Cook's letter. Two new iPhone apps this year. &lt;a href="https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2026/03/apple-to-celebrate-50-years-of-thinking-different/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded>
