Note: This is the same episode as "Deep Dive — AI 2027 Report: Reality Check" re-rendered using Kokoro TTS for voice quality comparison.
</description>
      <content:encoded>&lt;h2&gt;AI 2027 Report: Reality Check (Kokoro TTS Version)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A deep analysis of the AI 2027 forecasting report, examining predictions vs. 2026 reality. This version rendered with Kokoro TTS for A/B voice comparison against the original.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;What They Got Right&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agent development trajectory, coding AI as leading indicator, government remaining behind the curve, and safety risks becoming visible — all largely validated. &lt;a href="https://ai2027.org"&gt;Read the original report →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;What They Got Wrong&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Timeline (authors revised from 2027 to ~2030), competitive dynamics (DeepSeek undermined compute-concentration thesis), China prediction (private enterprise, not nationalization), smooth scaling thesis.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;The DeepSeek Surprise&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An under-resourced Chinese startup training frontier models for ~$6M was not in anyone's scenario planning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Overall Grade&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;B- for direction, D for timing. The &lt;em&gt;what&lt;/em&gt; is right even if the &lt;em&gt;when&lt;/em&gt; is wrong.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Kokoro TTS re-render — bonus episode for voice quality A/B comparison.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded>
