      <title>Week in Review — March 28, 2026</title>
      <description>Weekly briefing covering the week of March 22–28, 2026. Anthropic wins its landmark court case, Iran war escalates with Houthi entry, DHS shutdown worsens, and the week ahead is loaded.

00:00:00 Opening — The Week That Was
00:02:00 Highlights and Wins
00:03:15 Stories That Evolved
00:07:30 Vault Activity
00:08:30 Relationship Check
00:09:45 The Week Ahead
00:11:00 What to Watch
00:12:00 Closing</description>
      <content:encoded>&lt;h2&gt;The Week That Was&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This was Anthropic's week — a 43-page federal injunction, a leaked next-gen model (Claude Mythos), iOS 27 Siri integration, and $19B ARR. Meanwhile, the Iran war escalated: Houthis entered the conflict, oil hit $112.57, and Congress left for recess while 61,000 TSA workers remain unpaid.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Anthropic v. Pentagon&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Judge Rita Lin issued a preliminary injunction calling the Pentagon's designation "classic illegal First Amendment retaliation" and "Orwellian." Federal agencies can resume using Claude. The government has until April 2 to appeal. &lt;a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2026/03/26/anthropic-wins-preliminary-injunction-pentagon.html"&gt;CNBC coverage →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Iran War — Days 23–29&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The week opened with a 48-hour ultimatum and ended with Houthis firing on Israel. Oil surged from ~$102 to $112.57. Goldman Sachs says prices could stay elevated through 2027. The IEA called it worse than the 1970s oil shocks. &lt;a href="https://www.axios.com/2026/03/27/vance-iran-peace-talks"&gt;Axios: Vance takes lead →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;DHS Shutdown — Days 40–43&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Senate passed bipartisan funding at 2:20 AM Friday. House rejected it, passed their own bill, then both chambers left for two-week recess. No resolution before mid-April.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Apple&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;iOS 26.4 dropped with Playlist Playground and new emoji. AirPods Max 2 pre-orders opened. WWDC confirmed June 8. Bloomberg: iOS 27 will open Siri to Claude, Gemini via Extensions system. Apple turns 50 on Wednesday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;The Week Ahead&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ben arrives Monday for carpet install Tuesday. Karen's retirement announcement Wednesday (Q2 starts). Anthropic pilot discussion Thursday morning — same day as the government's appeal deadline and dinner with friends.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded>
