<item>
  <title>Saturday Afternoon Roundup — March 28, 2026</title>
  <description>Quick Saturday roundup: Claude subscriptions skyrocketing, Mac Pro discontinued, SoftBank's $40B OpenAI signal, YC Demo Day highlights, and Whoop's health monitoring pivot.</description>
  <content:encoded>&lt;h2&gt;Claude's Paying Users Have More Than Doubled&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anthropic reports explosive consumer growth in 2026, driven by Claude Code and smart marketing. &lt;a href="https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/28/anthropics-claude-popularity-with-paying-consumers-is-skyrocketing/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Apple Discontinues the Mac Pro&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Mac Pro has been pulled from Apple's website with no replacement announced. The Mac Studio effectively ate its market. &lt;a href="https://www.macstories.net/linked/apple-discontinues-the-mac-pro/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;SoftBank's $40B Loan Signals OpenAI IPO&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A 12-month unsecured loan to fund OpenAI investment suggests lenders expect a public offering within the year. &lt;a href="https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/27/why-softbanks-new-40b-loan-points-to-a-2026-openai-ipo/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;YC Demo Day Highlights&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From moon hotels to cattle herding — the Winter 2026 batch covered a wild range. &lt;a href="https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/28/from-moon-hotels-to-cattle-herding-8-startups-investors-chased-at-yc-demo-day/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Whoop Pivots to Health Monitoring&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The wearable company wants to move beyond elite athletes to become a life-saving health monitor for everyone. &lt;a href="https://techcrunch.com/2026/03/27/whoop-has-lebron-now-it-wants-your-mom/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded>
