    </item>
<item>
  <title>Apple TV+ 2026: The Complete Lineup</title>
  <description>A deep dive into everything coming to Apple TV+ in 2026 — returning favorites like Ted Lasso, Silo, and Slow Horses, plus new star-studded originals from Cape Fear to Lucky.</description>
  <content:encoded>
&lt;h2&gt;Returning Series&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Already premiered:&lt;/strong&gt; Hijack S2, Drops of God S2, Tehran S3, Shrinking S3, The Last Thing He Told Me S2, Monarch: Legacy of Monsters S2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Spring/Summer:&lt;/strong&gt; For All Mankind S5 (Mar 27), Your Friends &amp;amp; Neighbors S2 (Apr 3), Criminal Record S2 (Apr 22), Sugar S2 (Jun 19), Ted Lasso S4 (Summer), Silo S3 (Summer)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fall:&lt;/strong&gt; Slow Horses S6, The Morning Show S5&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;New Original Series&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eternity&lt;/strong&gt; (Feb 13) — Elizabeth Olsen, Miles Teller. Afterlife romantic comedy. &lt;a href="https://www.apple.com/tv-pr/news/2026/02/apple-tv-sets-must-see-2026-lineup-of-star-studded-original-series-films-and-live-sports/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Imperfect Women&lt;/strong&gt; (Mar 18) — Elisabeth Moss, Kerry Washington, Kate Mara. Psychological thriller. &lt;a href="https://collider.com/most-anticipated-apple-tv-shows-2026-ranked/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Margo's Got Money Troubles&lt;/strong&gt; (Apr 15) — Elle Fanning, Michelle Pfeiffer, Nicole Kidman. David E. Kelley comedy-drama. &lt;a href="https://www.apple.com/tv-pr/news/2026/02/apple-tv-sets-must-see-2026-lineup-of-star-studded-original-series-films-and-live-sports/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Widow's Bay&lt;/strong&gt; (Apr 29) — Matthew Rhys. Horror-comedy. &lt;a href="https://www.thewrap.com/creative-content/tv-shows/apple-tv-film-series-slate-2026/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maximum Pleasure Guaranteed&lt;/strong&gt; (May 20) — Tatiana Maslany. Dark comedy thriller. &lt;a href="https://www.thewrap.com/creative-content/tv-shows/apple-tv-film-series-slate-2026/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cape Fear&lt;/strong&gt; (Jun 5) — Javier Bardem, Amy Adams. Scorsese reimagining. &lt;a href="https://www.apple.com/tv-pr/news/2026/02/apple-tv-sets-must-see-2026-lineup-of-star-studded-original-series-films-and-live-sports/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lucky&lt;/strong&gt; (Jul 15) — Anya Taylor-Joy, Annette Bening, Timothy Olyphant. Limited series. &lt;a href="https://collider.com/most-anticipated-apple-tv-shows-2026-ranked/"&gt;Read more →&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Notable Films&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Outcome (Apr 10) — Keanu Reeves, Cameron Diaz, Martin Scorsese&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Dink (Jul 24) — Pickleball comedy with Ben Stiller&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mayday (Sep 4) — Ryan Reynolds, Kenneth Branagh&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matchbox The Movie (Oct 9) — John Cena&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Way of the Warrior Kid (Nov 20) — Chris Pratt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;What's NOT Coming in 2026&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Severance S3 — Filming starts spring 2026, likely mid-2027 premiere&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bad Sisters S3 — Not renewed; creator says S2 was a natural endpoint&lt;/p&gt;
