      <title>Daily Briefing — Saturday Evening Update, March 28, 2026</title>
      <description>Trump extends Hormuz deadline 10 days. Dubai crude hits $126. Iranian Red Crescent reports 1,900 killed. TSA paychecks may arrive Monday. Bank of America settles Epstein lawsuit for $72.5M. Anthropic nears $19B annualized revenue. Apple partners with Google Gemini for Siri overhaul.</description>
      <content:encoded>&lt;h2&gt;Iran War — Evening Update&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Trump extended the Strait of Hormuz deadline by 10 days — Iran now has until ~April 7 to reopen the strait. Dubai crude benchmark at $126/barrel, up 76% since the war started. Pakistan now acting as intermediary. Iranian Red Crescent: 1,900 killed since Feb 28. In Lebanon, 1,142 killed including 122 children.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;DHS Shutdown&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;TSA workers should start seeing paychecks as early as Monday, March 30.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Financial&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bank of America agreed to pay $72.5M to settle Epstein-related lawsuit. Anthropic approaching $19B annualized revenue.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Apple&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Apple partnering with Google to use 1.2T parameter Gemini model for reimagined Siri in iOS 26.4.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded>
