      <title>Daily Briefing — Saturday Mid-Morning Update, March 28, 2026</title>
      <description>Houthis enter Iran war. 3,100+ No Kings protests planned. Warhorse Studios fires translator for AI. Apple turns 50 Wednesday. Cherry blossoms in Tacoma.</description>
      <content:encoded>&lt;h2&gt;Weather&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jefferson City: frost at dawn (31°F), climbing to 83°F with full sun. Tacoma: 56°F, partly cloudy, rain tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Texts&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Katelyn asking about bird sightings — you two have been trading all week. Alex sent The Verge's Apple 50th anniversary product ranking at 11 PM Friday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Iran War Escalation&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Houthis launched their first military operation in support of Iran — a ballistic missile at Israel. Debris caused fires at a UAE industrial hub. Drone hit Kuwait airport radar. The 10-day Hormuz extension is the framework but the situation is more fragile.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;No Kings Protests&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;3,100+ demonstrations planned nationwide, organizers expecting millions. Two-thirds of RSVPs from outside major cities, up 40% from June 2025.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;DHS Shutdown Day 43&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Congress left for two-week recess without a deal. 61,000 TSA workers have missed three paychecks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;AI Replacement Watch&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Warhorse Studios (Kingdom Come Deliverance 2) fired their Czech-to-English translator and replaced him with AI. No warning. 12K upvotes, 1,500 comments on Reddit.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Apple&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Turns 50 Wednesday. iPhone Air C1X modem matches Qualcomm on speed, wins on latency. 15+ new products expected this year. No iPhone in Lockdown Mode has ever been hacked.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;From Your Inbox&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Claude Team: Claude Code can now keep working while you're away. 404 Media: Earth's magnetic field creating cosmic ray void. The Atlantic: America sliding toward illiteracy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Tacoma&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Cherry blossoms blooming at Wapato Hills — gorgeous photos on r/Tacoma.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded>
