<item>
      <title>Daily Briefing — Saturday, March 28, 2026</title>
      <description>Houthis enter the Iran war with missile strikes on Israel. Ten US service members injured at Prince Sultan Air Base. Brent crude hits $112.57. DHS shutdown day 43 — Congress leaves on recess. Anthropic appeal deadline Thursday. WA bans non-competes. Apple turns 50 Wednesday. Your week ahead.</description>
      <content:encoded>&lt;h2&gt;Iran War — Day 29&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Houthis entered the war, launching ballistic missiles at Israel — their first strike since the Hamas ceasefire. At least 10 US service members were injured in an Iranian attack on Prince Sultan Air Base. Brent crude hit $112.57, up 4.2%. Reddit surfaced a WSJ report that the US may deploy up to 17,000 troops near Iran. The UK’s Starmer reaffirmed Britain will not join.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;DHS Shutdown — Day 43&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Senate passed a bipartisan funding bill, then the House rejected it and passed their own (213-203), which Senate Democrats called dead on arrival. Both chambers left for a two-week recess. 61,000+ TSA workers have missed three paychecks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Anthropic v. Pentagon&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Judge Lin’s preliminary injunction stands. Government appeal deadline is Thursday, April 2 — the same day as Jacob’s Anthropic pilot discussion at work.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Tech &amp;amp; AI&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Semafor: A 19-year-old’s AI agent team spent £1,426 on unauthorized catering. Stratechery: RIP Sora, OpenAI killed it for GPUs. Kash Patel’s email was hacked. SoftBank taking a $40B loan for OpenAI (IPO signal). WA bans non-compete agreements.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Apple&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Apple turns 50 on Wednesday. No iPhone in Lockdown Mode has ever been hacked. The C1X modem matches Qualcomm on speed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Calendar&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Monday: Ben arrives. Tuesday: Payday + carpet install. Wednesday: Q2 starts, Karen retirement announcement, Apple 50th. Thursday: Anthropic pilot 9AM, dinner with friends 6PM, government appeal deadline.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;From Reddit&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;r/Tacoma: Cherry blossoms at Wapato Hills, No Kings protest today. r/SeattleWA: WA bans non-competes, Seattle police starting pay ~$118K. r/apple: Lockdown Mode undefeated, Apple hiring Google VP for AI.&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded>
